<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40029a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40029a">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40029a"> 29(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ferment</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Upon this an American writer has commented thus: &ldquo;I can testify that, while travelling five thousand miles in India, I never saw any agricultural implement not used by the sons of Abraham three thousand years ago. They reap with a sickle and thresh with a flail that was old when Methuselah was a child.&rdquo; <font color="green">[Footnote attributes this to Dr. Claud H. Van Tyne in &ldquo;India in Ferment.&rdquo;]</font> <small> Rev W.S. Hunt, <a name="WSHI1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WSHI1"><cite title="source">India's Outcastes: A New Era</cite></a> (1924) 29</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
